<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Male, wingspan 28 mm (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Adults of Sacada spp. 1 S. sikkima (Moore) (male), India 2 S. sikkima (Moore) (male), lectotype, Darjeeling, India 3 S. constrictalis (Ragonot) (male), India 4, 5 S. discinota (Moore) (male), India 6 S. discinota (Moore) (male), lectotype, Darjeeling, India. Scale bars: 5 mm (1); 12.7 mm (3 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443709" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Adults of Sacada spp. 1 S. sikkima (Moore) (male), India 2 S. sikkima (Moore) (male), lectotype, Darjeeling, India 3 S. constrictalis (Ragonot) (male), India 4, 5 S. discinota (Moore) (male), India 6 S. discinota (Moore) (male), lectotype, Darjeeling, India. Scale bars: 5 mm (1); 12.7 mm (3 - 5)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443709" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">2</figureCitation>
). Adult dark purplish fuscous. Forewing with a dark rufous rectangular patch near base, touching antemedial line which is highly angled in interno-median interspace; postmedial line pale, sinuous, outwardly oblique from costa to vein M2, then very oblique to inner margin; area between antemedial and postmedial line paler and beyond postmedial line darker. Hindwing pale brown; a pale, slightly waved submarginal line crossed by a dark streak at vein Cu1. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 19, 20 Male genitalia of S. sikkima (Moore) 21, 22 male genitalia of S. constrictalis (Ragonot) 23, 24 male genitalia of S. discinota (Moore) 25, 26 male genitalia of S. unilinealis Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443712" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 19, 20 Male genitalia of S. sikkima (Moore) 21, 22 male genitalia of S. constrictalis (Ragonot) 23, 24 male genitalia of S. discinota (Moore) 25, 26 male genitalia of S. unilinealis Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443712" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">20</figureCitation>
). Uncus broad with flaps on lateral side, gnathos reaching up to tip of uncus, tip hooked; valva simple, without any process; tegumen simple; transtilla broad with sclerotised, bifid process originating medially; juxta in form of two long arms, broad medially, spined apically; saccus deeply U-shaped; vesica membranous with fine scobination, without any cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Sacada" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sacada sikkima" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Sacada sikkima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is externally similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. constrictalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="constrictalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">S. constrictalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from India, but differs by its larger size, and in having the postmedial line outwardly oblique from the costa to vein M2, whereas, in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. constrictalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="constrictalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">S. constrictalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the postmedial lines is almost straight. In the male genitalia (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 19, 20 Male genitalia of S. sikkima (Moore) 21, 22 male genitalia of S. constrictalis (Ragonot) 23, 24 male genitalia of S. discinota (Moore) 25, 26 male genitalia of S. unilinealis Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443712" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Male genitalia of Sacada spp. 19, 20 Male genitalia of S. sikkima (Moore) 21, 22 male genitalia of S. constrictalis (Ragonot) 23, 24 male genitalia of S. discinota (Moore) 25, 26 male genitalia of S. unilinealis Hampson." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.962.51194.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443712" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">20</figureCitation>
), the transtillar processes are longer; the juxta is larger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
